-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/turkey-s-otokar-falls-after-third-quarter-profit-declines-77-.html
Otokar Otomotiv & Savunma Sanayi AS,
a producer of minibuses and military trucks, dropped to the
lowest in more than two weeks after reporting third-quarter
profit fell 77 percent.  The shares dropped 1.4 percent to close at 34.30 liras in
Istanbul trading, the lowest since Oct. 4.  Third-quarter profit was 2.35 million liras ($1.28
million), compared with 10.1 million liras in the same period of
2010, the company said in a statement to the exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
